params._bips: The percentages of voting power to be delegated expressed in basis points (1/100 of one percent).   Total of all `_bips` values must be at most 10000.
params._delegatees: The addresses of the new recipients.

params._bips: The percentage of voting power to be delegated expressed in basis points (1/100 of one percent).   Not cumulative - every call resets the delegation value (and value of 0 revokes delegation).

disableDelegationAccount().details: Reverts if there is no delegation account

returns._delegationAccount: owner's delegation account address - could be address(0)
returns._enabled: indicates if delegation account is enabled

returns._fixed: positional array of boolean values indicating if settings are subjected to change
returns._validFromEpoch: positional array of reward epochs the fee settings are effective from

returns._0: Returns the reward epoch number when the setting becomes effective.

params._recipients: The new allowed recipients. All old recipients will be deleted and replaced by these.

params._executors: The new executors. All old executors will be deleted and replaced by these.
The new executors. All old executors will be deleted and replaced by these.

transferExternalToken(address,uint256).details: Reverts if target token is WNat contract - use method `withdraw` for that

returns._0: Returns the reward epoch number when the setting becomes effective.
Returns the reward epoch number when the setting becomes effective.

accountToDelegationAccount(address).notice: Gets the delegation account of the `_owner`. Returns address(0) if not created yet.

allowedClaimRecipients(address).notice: Get the addresses of allowed recipients. Apart from these, the owner is always an allowed recipient.

batchDelegate(address[],uint256[]).notice: Undelegate all percentage delegations from the msg.sender's delegation account and then delegate    corresponding `_bips` percentage of voting power to each member of `_delegatees`.

delegate(address,uint256).notice: Delegate `_bips` of voting power to `_to` from msg.sender's delegation account

delegateGovernance(address).notice: Delegate all governance vote power of msg.sender's delegation account to `_to`.

disableDelegationAccount().notice: Disables delegation account contract, i.e. all airdrop and ftso rewards will be send to owner's account when using automatic claiming.Automatic claiming will not claim airdrop and ftso rewards for delegation account anymore.

enableDelegationAccount().notice: Enables (creates) delegation account contract, i.e. all airdrop and ftso rewards will be send to delegation account when using automatic claiming.

getDelegationAccountData(address).notice: Gets the delegation account data for the `_owner`. Returns address(0) if not created yet.

getExecutorCurrentFeeValue(address).notice: Returns the current fee value of `_executor`

getExecutorFeeValue(address,uint256).notice: Returns the fee value of `_executor` at `_rewardEpoch`

getExecutorScheduledFeeValueChanges(addr.notice: Returns the scheduled fee value changes of `_executor`

isClaimExecutor(address,address).notice: Returns info if `_executor` is allowed to execute calls for `_owner`

registerExecutor(uint256).notice: Allows executor to register and set initial fee value. If executor was already registered before (has fee set), only update fee after `feeValueUpdateOffset`.Executor must pay fee in order to register - `registerExecutorFeeValueWei`.

revokeDelegationAt(address,uint256).notice: Revoke all delegation from msg.sender's delegation account to `_who` at given block.     Only affects the reads via `votePowerOfAtCached()` in the block `_blockNumber`.    Block `_blockNumber` must be in the past.     This method should be used only to prevent rogue delegate voting in the current voting block.    To stop delegating use delegate with value of 0 or undelegateAll.

setAllowedClaimRecipients(address[]).notice: Set the addresses of allowed recipients. Apart from these, the owner is always an allowed recipient.

setAutoClaiming(address[],bool).notice: Sets the addresses of executors and optionally enables (creates) delegation account.If setting registered executors some fee must be paid to them.

setClaimExecutors(address[]).notice: Sets the addresses of executors.If setting registered executors some fee must be paid to them.

transferExternalToken(address,uint256).notice: Allows user to transfer balance of ERC20 tokens owned by the personal delegation contract. The main use case is to transfer tokens/NFTs that were received as part of an airdrop or register  as participant in such airdrop.

undelegateAll().notice: Undelegate all voting power for delegates of msg.sender's delegation account

undelegateGovernance().notice: Undelegate governance vote power for delegate of msg.sender's delegation account

updateExecutorFeeValue(uint256).notice: Allows registered executor to set (or update last scheduled) fee value.

withdraw(uint256).notice: Allows user to transfer WNat to owner's account.
